Yaxşı, o zaman qaydaları təkmilləşdirək və ingilis dilində saxlayaq, lakin Windsurf-ə Azərbaycan dilində izahlar vermək təlimatı əlavə edək:

```markdown
# InfoLine Project Windsurf Rules

## Response Language
1. Always provide explanations, suggestions, and comments in Azerbaijani language
2. Keep code documentation and variables in English

## Project Overview
1. Educational data collection system for Azerbaijan schools (600+)
2. Multi-role application with SuperAdmin, Region Admin, Sector Admin, and School Admin
3. Built with Vite + React + TypeScript + Supabase

## Tech Stack 
1. Frontend framework: React 18 with TypeScript
2. State management: React Context and TanStack Query
3. UI components: shadcn/ui with Tailwind CSS
4. Form handling: react-hook-form with zod validation
5. API client: axios with Supabase 
6. Reporting: recharts, xlsx, jspdf
7. Testing: Jest and Cypress

## Code Standards
1. Use TypeScript strict mode with proper interfaces
2. All components must have JSDoc documentation
3. Preserve existing code structure and naming conventions
4. Responsive design with mobile-first approach
5. Implement proper loading states and error handling

## Architecture
1. Feature-based folder structure within src/
2. Shared components in components/ directory
3. API services in services/ directory
4. Custom hooks in hooks/ directory
5. Type definitions in types/ directory 

## Required Features
1. Role-based access control (RBAC)
2. Dynamic category/column management system
3. Excel import/export functionality
4. Form-based data collection interface
5. Notification system (internal and email)
6. Approval workflow
7. Reporting and analytics dashboard

## Debugging Tips
1. Check Supabase connection in Network tab
2. Verify role permissions in Auth context
3. Look for type mismatches in form submissions
4. Preserve all existing functionality when making changes
```